The paper deals with two important subfields of artificial intelligence, namely analogical reasoning and kernel-based machine learning. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also introduces a new method based on support vector machines trained with the analogy kernel, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG sub-category. The paper deals with object ranking in the realm of preference learning, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CC sub-category. The paper also deals with data sets from different domains, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.IR sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CL sub-category.
